# BOLOOT Persian Calendar — Architecture

**Display name:** `BOLOOT Persian Calendar`  
**Website:** [boloot.ir](https://boloot.ir)

## Workspace layout
- `core/` — calendar, prayer, holidays, locale, formatting, `brand.rs` (APP_NAME, WEBSITE)
- `daemon/` — D-Bus session service (`org.boloot.Calendar`)
- `cli/` — `boloot-calendar-ctl` binary
- `gnome-shell/` — GNOME Shell top-bar extension (`boloot-calendar@boloot.ir`)
- `settings/` — GTK4 + libadwaita settings app
- `data/` — embedded holidays and city locations

## Separation of concerns
- All date/time/locale formatting lives in `core`; UI layers only display strings from D-Bus or CLI.
- Config: `~/.config/boloot-calendar/config.toml` (XDG). Data: `/usr/share/boloot-calendar/data` or `BOLOOT_DATA_DIR`.
- Errors: `thiserror` + `BolootError` in `core`; `anyhow` in binaries only.
- User-facing name: always `BOLOOT Persian Calendar`; show `boloot.ir` in about/footer.

## Do not
- Format dates or numerals in JS/Python UI code.
- Write to `/etc` without Polkit/privilege separation.
- Hardcode country-specific logic outside `locale.rs` / country profiles.
